		<img width="2500" height="1200" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools-1536x737.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools-2048x983.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-hammerhead-shakr-schools-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Scalloped hammerhead sharks are critically endangered. But the discovery of a schooling population in the Caribbean is giving local researchers hope. Blickwinkel/Alamy Stock Photo</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">In the Caribbean, Hammerhead Sharks Return to School</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">The detection of schooling behavior is a promising sign of recovery for this iconic and endangered animal.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/david-shiffman/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >David Shiffman</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						May 8, 2024 | 550 words, about 2 minutes
					</aside>

					
